Privacy Policy for Road Kit
Effective date: 16.09.2025
Batulin Tymur (“we”, “our”, “us”) built the Road Kit app as a tool for travelers who want to compare traffic rules
and plan driving routes across supported countries. This Privacy Policy explains how the app handles user
information.
Information Collection and Use
- The app does not collect, store, or share any personal information such as names, emails, or contact details.
- The app uses device location solely for the purpose of building driving routes. All processing happens locally
on your device. Location data is never transmitted to external servers or third parties.
Data Sharing
- We do not share or sell any data to third parties.
- The app does not include advertising or third-party analytics services.
Offline Functionality
Road Kit is designed to work offline. Your information remains entirely on your device.
Children’s Privacy
The app does not knowingly collect any personal information from children under 13. Since no data is collected,
the app is safe for all age groups.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in this section with a new
“Effective date.”
